Original Project: py-ran-task
Source URL: https://github.com/bnicenboim/py-ran-task
Original License: GPL-2.0 (see LICENSE file)
Original Author: Bruno Nicenboim (adapted from Titus Von der Malsburg)

Modifications made to the original code:

1. Framework Change
   - Replaced Tkinter GUI with PsychoPy for stimulus presentation
   - Changed from tkSnack to sounddevice + soundfile for audio recording

2. Configuration System
   - Replaced Python config files with YAML-based configuration
   - Config loaded from config.yaml and experiment.yaml

3. Task Type
   - Changed from letters + numbers to numbers only
   - Added digits.yaml with digit matrices

4. Data Output
   - Changed from text files to CSV format
   - Audio saved as WAV files with participant/trial metadata
   - Modified output path structure: data/{participant_folder}/RAN/

5. Code Structure
   - Converted from single script to modular structure
   - Added command-line argument parsing (--participant_folder)
   - Added instruction loading from Excel files
   - Added escape key support for early exit

